623	Lottie	Shackelford			http://www.encyclopediaofarkansas.net/encyclopedia/entry-detail.aspx?entryID=4841	623	Lottie Shackelford, born in 1941, was the first black woman elected the mayor of a major American city (Little Rock, Arkansas, 1987.) She had a custodial job and then worked for The League of Greater Little Rock, the Economic Opportunity Agency to fight poverty, and the Opportunities Industrialization Center, which gave job opportunities to African Americans. She became a part of the democratic party and worked for political reforms and overseas projects: The United Nations Commission on the Status of Women in Vienna and the Board of Directors on the Overseas Private Investment corporation. In these organizations she recognized women's advancement in the world and encouraged US businesses to invest in developing countries.\n	2016-08-25 17:40:20.626359	\N	f	t	1	https://lrculturevulture.files.wordpress.com/2014/04/mayor-lottie_shackelford.jpg?w=269&h=300\n	N/A
